    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras face a high-variance slate today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (75.76) and **Junior Caminero** (73.35). **Yordan Alvarez** remains our most potent asset, drawing a +14% park boost that overrides his standard platoon disadvantage against left-hander Kyle Freeland. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** benefits from a soft matchup against Assad, with his elite SP skill adjustment pushing him well into the strong-start tier. **Colt Keith** (67.82), **Trea Turner** (70.39), and **Kyle Schwarber** (69.61) also provide excellent stability at the top of our lineup; **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** are particularly enticing given the wind-out conditions, which maximize their fly-ball profiles against the veteran Robbie Ray.\n\nOur strategy for stolen bases leans on **Victor Scott II** (51.62) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (56.38), both of whom offer marginal value today but remain essential to maintaining our category lead. While **Victor Scott II** is buried in the #9 hole, his efficiency against Cavalli keeps him active. The most difficult benching decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion** (40.21), who was considered for the UTIL slot. Despite his power potential, the combination of facing a high-caliber arm in Cristopher S\u00e1nchez and an unfavorable #7 batting order pushed his score below our threshold for active play. We are monitoring **Trea Turner**, **Kyle Schwarber**, **Logan O'Hoppe**, and **Yordan Alvarez** closely, as their scores are contingent on \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions; any deviation from these projected spots\u2014particularly if **Trea Turner** or **Kyle Schwarber** move down in the order\u2014could necessitate a shift in our late-game management to preserve our game caps.",
